#: ../../effects_and_compositions/effect_groups/alpha_manipulation/blue_screen.rst:56
msgid "See also"
msgstr "Pozri aj"

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/effect_groups/alpha_manipulation/blue_screen.rst:60
msgid ""
"See also :ref:`rotoscoping` effect. Rotoscoping is where you manual draw a"
" region, and everything outside/inside that region will disappear. This is"
" useful for backgrounds with multiple different colours."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/effect_groups/alpha_manipulation/blue_screen.rst:63
msgid ""
"See also :ref:`keysplillm0pup` effect in the Misc group. The Key Spill Mop Up"
" effect can be used to improve the edges of the blue screen effect - when"
" edge problems are caused by \"keyspill\". Keyspill is when the color of the"
" screen used for colorkeying spills onto the subject due to light reflection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/effect_groups/alpha_manipulation/blue_screen.rst:66
msgid ""
"See also :ref:`color_selection` which also does color based alpha selection,"
" but in a much more detailed fashion. Use it for less contrasting or more"
" complex backgrounds."
msgstr ""
